Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-anon
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-anon
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Anonymization & Data Masking for PostgreSQL
  PostgreSQL Anonymizer is an extension to mask or replace personally identifiable information (PII)
  or commercially sensitive data from a Postgres database.
  The project has a declarative approach of anonymization. This means you can
  declare the masking rules using the PostgreSQL Data Definition Language (DDL)
  and specify your anonymization policy inside the table definition itself.
